left_text: Vertex of head between lateral ocellus and eye slightly rounded to ﬂat as seen in frontal view, at most with shallow depression; ﬁrst ﬂagellar segment of male conspicuously widened apically, as in female; sclerotized apex of female S6 with spinelike setae absent or short (Fig. 103-2a), barely visible at low magniﬁcation, lateral apical margin not expanded, not folded down; apex of female T5 without membranous rim; male S6 with large preapical tubercle
